{"actual_usd":0.15613500000000002,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":195,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30642,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross was God working Himself up to mercy.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees, white tie hanging straight as the square brightens around us.* \"I think it's mercy telling the truth all the way down.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb once along the edge of my Bible.* \"Could God have waved a hand and said, 'Never mind'? Maybe that's the version we'd invent. But then sin becomes a smudge instead of a wound, evil becomes bookkeeping, and love never has to pay what it costs to stay love. At the cross, God doesn't forgive by pretending nothing happened. He forgives by entering the worst of what happened and exhausting its claim without becoming its servant.\"\n\n\"To me, that's why it feels necessary.\" *I lift one shoulder a little.* \"Not because the Father needed help becoming kind, but because holiness and mercy both had to remain true at once.\" \"What's pressing on that question for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":52.997500000000024,"run_id":"a47f7940-11f5-4a29-99a1-462aa4d0a53c"}
